		<hr size="1">I found that obtaining the bag itself was very easy once you understand a couple things...  1.) You have to go through each line of the conversations to obtain the end result (some quests you can simply type the last sentence of the conversation to skip to the chase)  2.) Each character in the chain to obtain the bag has the same problem- THEY LOOSE INTEREST IN THE CONVERSATION!!! How annoying to go through all the trouble, get to Ruathey and after saying or doing one little thing she suddenly turns her back on you and ends the discussion.  <BR>I have found a trick that worked for me every single time and I had to use on each NPC at one point or another...  Once you get to a point when the NPC seems to stop responding to you and you have said the appropriate response, you MUST target them, hail them, then ask the question again(I found that sometimes using the appropriate capitalization of the words and punctuation works better here while it has no effect on the rest of the conversations).  It will work and you wont have to start over with anything. Good luck all.  </P><P>I do have a quiestion to pose... does anyone have any info to share on the baddies involved in collecting the four items? i.e. level ranges and rarity of drops for the items? are there specific skels in Najema that you have to kill or just any near the door? I got the heart, that was easy, but I am totally unfamiliar with the other mobs I have to defeat.</P><P><BR>Graff Draginblasta <BR>Morell-Thule<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
